{
  "question": "How does social media affect our decision-making process?",
  "answer": "Social media alters how we make choices, how we spend our time, which products we buy, and more."
}

{
  "question": "Evaluate the significance of scarcity.",
  "answer": "Scarcity is significant because it limits the production of goods and services and affects access to critical resources like food, housing, and healthcare."
}

{
  "question": "What are the three reasons Smith offered for how a group of specialized workers can produce more than the same number of workers who try to produce the entire good or service by themselves?",
  "answer": "The three reasons are workers specialize in particular tasks where they have an advantage, workers who specialize work faster and produce higher quality, and businesses take advantage of economies of scale."
}

